nearest(x, s) returns the nearest representable number to x
in the direction of the sign of s.

default real examples:
x = -1
  nearest(x,  1.0) = -0.9999999
  nearest(x, -1.0) = -1
x = 0
  nearest(x,  1.0) = 1.401298e-45
  nearest(x, -1.0) = -1.401298e-45
x = 1
  nearest(x,  1.0) = 1
  nearest(x, -1.0) = 0.9999999
x = 10
  nearest(x,  1.0) = 10
  nearest(x, -1.0) = 9.999999
x = 3.402823e+38
  nearest(x,  1.0) = inf
  nearest(x, -1.0) = 3.402823e+38

kind examples:
nearest(1.0_4,  1.0_4) = 1
nearest(1.0_4, -1.0_4) = 0.9999999

nearest(1.0_8,  1.0_8) = 1
nearest(1.0_8, -1.0_8) = 1
